Release Date: 27th February 2024

Canadian producer and live act CRi unveils his ‘Miracles’ (Remixed) album. The package features unreleased remixes from Nicky Elisabeth, Dj Cinéma Quartier Latin and Jesse Mac Cormack, alongside reworks from Jacques Greene, Romain Garcia, Qrion, Amtrac and CRi himself.

‘Miracles’ garnered over 23M streams in the seven months since its release and was followed by a 17-date North American album tour at the end of 2023, which included a stop at Montréal’s iconic venue MTELUS. This year, CRi kicked off his second run of album tour dates with a sold-out headline show at London’s Lafayette, and will shortly be travelling to perform in countries including Hong Kong and India.

Following a recent remix of Yotto and Lost Boy’s ‘Just The Kinda Feeling’ released on Yotto’s label Odd One Out and a string of shows across the US and Canada supporting CRi on his album tour, Nicky is poised to have an even busier 2024. She begins a year full of new music and Anjunadeep label event appearances with a rework of CRi’s ‘Astray’, that is filled with lush synths, and that plays with Half Moon Run’s vocals; turning the original into an uplifting dancefloor record.

Montréal-based producer and touring act Dj Cinéma Quartier Latin also stars on the ‘Miracles’ (Remixed) album, and unveils an energetic remix of ‘Astray’ with a lively bassline that drives through a confident percussive track.

Closing the remix album is CRi’s longstanding collaborator and friend Jesse Mac Cormack who delivers an energetic and up-tempo rework of ‘Memories’, featuring Sophia Bel, adding in commanding drums and shifting synths. Previously, Jesse has produced for numerous artists including Helena Deland, Rosie Valland, Phillipe Brach, Sara-Danielle and Lonny, and also boasts two solo albums ‘Now’ and ‘SOLO’. Always an energetic presence at CRi’s special live shows, Jesse is set to embark on his own mini tour around Quebec in March 2024.

CRi’s ‘Miracles’ (Remixed) is out February 27 on Anjunadeep.
